1. Create a conda env dedicated to this project. Command: conda create -n wineq python=3.7 -y
2. Activate the new env. Command: activate wineq
3. Create requirements.txt with all the required packages
2. run command pip install -r requirements.txt
3. Create the template that is the folder structure for the project
. push the data into history github: git init
4. dvc init: initialize the dvc that is creating .dvc folder
5. To track the data we will exe the command: dvc add data_given\winequality.csv
-> this will keep a version of the data in the form of winequality.csv.dvc
git add. :This command will add all the details in the current direc to the staging area
git commit -m "Firt Commit": it is used to commit the data in staging area
